choice. You'll have to join the Princess Mountain
Defense Squad too. If you do that, you'll be able
to enter the secret base too.

\N<Boku>Eh!? Is that so!? Yeah! Then, I also want

\N<Boy>It's the Princess Mountain Defense Squad.
However, you can't join so easily. You'll have to
undergo a rigorous entrance exam.

\N<Boy>I got it. If you can beat me in a 'Bug
Battle,' I'll allow you to join.

\N<Boy>What's the matter, don't you know? It's the
hottest game right now where you make the beetles
you caught, like stag beetles and rhinoceros
beetles, fight each other.
\N<Boku>Is that so... but I don't have any bugs...

\N<Boy>I guess there's no other choice. Here, I'll
lend you this 'bug net,' so go ahead and catch
something. There were stag beetles around here
earlier.
\N<Boku>Wow! Thanks! Then, I'll try catching them!

I obtained a plaything. When you have obtained a
plaything, you can switch it with the W key and Q
key, and use the item with the confirm button.

When you press the W key, it will cycle through
the following order: bare hands -> tool 1 -> tool
2 -> tool 3 -> bare hands. When you press the Q
key, it will cycle in the opposite order.

You can catch bugs by using a bug net and fish by
using a fishing rod, depending on the target.
However, you cannot use playthings like these
inside the house.

Also, please note that you cannot talk to or
examine things while holding a tool. You can
confirm the above explanation in the instruction
manual as well.

Let's quickly grab the 'bug net' and try catching
the 'bugs' flying around or perched on trees.

\N<Boy>If you swing the bug net towards the bugs,
you can catch them. Since bugs are small, you have
to search carefully. They might be flying around
or perched on a tree, shining black.

\N<Boy>Oh? Did you catch a sawtooth stag beetle?
Then let's have a bug battle right away!
\N<Boku>Um... How do we do bug battles?

\N<Boy>Hmm... Listen carefully, the basics of bug
battles are like a one-on-one rock-paper-scissors
game.

\N<Boy>That's right, rock-paper-scissors. There
are four commands you can give to your bug.
Attack, special move, barrier, and charge.

\N<Boku>Huh? Barrier...? Can bugs really do
something like that...?

\N<Boy>Use your imagination. You must have played
pretend games before, right? Like playing tag, for
example. Can you really become the demon in a game
of tag?

\N<Boy>If you understand, then that's good. Well
then, I'll continue with the explanation.

\N<Boy>First, attacks are strong against barriers,
but weak against special moves.

\N<Boy>Finishing moves are strong against attacks,
but weak against barriers.

\N<Boy>Barriers are strong against finishing
moves, but weak against attacks.

\N<Boy>And finally, Charge is weak against
everything, but it slightly restores the bug's
stamina and increases its attack power for the
next turn.

\N<Boy>One thing to be careful of is that
finishing moves require 'Move Points' and cannot
be used when they run out.

\N<Boy>Also, you can't give the same command twice
in a row.

\N<Boy>This rule applies to both you and your
opponent, so think carefully about what the
opponent will do next and give instructions to the
bug.

\N<Boy>The one who reduces the opponent's bug's HP
to zero first wins. Oh, and if the bug moves back
with an 'Attack' or 'Finishing Move', falling off
the ring also counts as a loss.

\N<Boy>Well, it would be faster if we actually
tried it. Don't worry, I'll go easy on you.

\N<Boy>Oh, and don't forget that the bug at the
front of your team will participate in the battle.
Well then, let's get started quickly.

\N<Boy>Well, I guess there's no helping it. Listen
carefully.

During the Bug Battle, you can change the speed of
the Bug Battle by pressing the Shift key. When in
Speed Up mode, a music note symbol will be
displayed in the upper left corner.

Boy: Huh...? I don't have a bug... Let's battle
with this bug.

When you select Bug Cage from the menu, you can

when you select Bug Training, you can use Training
Points to level up your bugs.

If you don't have enough points for leveling up,
you won't be able to select it. Training Points
